Events#

Documentation of all available library events. See how to use them: Events Example

pynext.on_user_ready(selfbot)#

Called when the selfbot connects to the gateway and completes chunking.

Parameters:

selfbot (SelfBot) – Selfbot that is ready.

pynext.on_channel_create(selfbot, channel)#

Called when a channel has been created.

Parameters:

  • selfbot (SelfBot) – Selfbot that received an event from the websocket.

  • channel (Union[GuildChannel, DMChannel]) – Created channel.

pynext.on_channel_edit(selfbot, old, new)#

Called when a channel has been edited.

Note

If the channel is not found in the internal cache, then this event will not be called.

Parameters:

  • selfbot (SelfBot) – Selfbot that received an event from the websocket.

  • old (Union[GuildChannel, DMChannel]) – Old channel object.

  • new (Union[GuildChannel, DMChannel]) – New channel object.

pynext.on_channel_delete(selfbot, channel)#

Called when a channel has been deleted.

Note

If the channel is not found in the internal cache, then this event will not be called.

Parameters:

  • selfbot (SelfBot) – Selfbot that received an event from the websocket.

  • channel (Union[GuildChannel, DMChannel]) – Deleted channel.

pynext.on_message_create(selfbot, message)#

Called when a Message is created and sent.

Parameters:

  • selfbot (SelfBot) – Selfbot that received an event from the websocket.

  • message (Union[GuildMessage, PrivateMessage]) – Received message.

pynext.on_message_edit(selfbot, old, new)#

Called when the message has been edited.

Note

If old message is not found in the internal cache, then this event will not be called.

Parameters:

  • selfbot (SelfBot) – Selfbot that received an event from the websocket.

  • old (Union[GuildMessage, PrivateMessage]) – Old message object.

  • new (Union[GuildMessage, PrivateMessage]) – New message object.

pynext.on_message_delete(selfbot, message)#

Called when a message has been deleted.

Note

If the message is not found in the internal cache, then this event will not be called.

Parameters:

  • selfbot (SelfBot) – Selfbot that received an event from the websocket.

  • message (Union[GuildMessage, PrivateMessage]) – Deleted message.

pynext.on_message_reaction_add(selfbot, reaction)#

Called when a reaction is added to a message.

Parameters:

  • selfbot (SelfBot) – Selfbot that received an event from the websocket.

  • reaction (MessageReaction) – Added reaction.

pynext.on_message_reaction_remove(selfbot, reaction)#

Called when the reaction is removed from the message.

Parameters:

  • selfbot (SelfBot) – Selfbot that received an event from the websocket.

  • reaction (MessageReaction) – Removed reaction.

pynext.on_guild_create(selfbot, guild)#

Called when Guild became available, or selfbot joined a new guild.

Parameters:

  • selfbot (SelfBot) – Selfbot that received an event from the websocket.

  • guild (Guild) – Guild object.

pynext.on_guild_edit(selfbot, old, new)#

Called when guild will be updated.

Note

If the Guild is not found in the internal cache, then this event will not be called.

Parameters:

  • selfbot (SelfBot) – Selfbot that received an event from the websocket.

  • old (Guild) – Old guild object.

  • new (Guild) – New guild object.

pynext.on_guild_delete(selfbot, guild)#

Called when a guild has been deleted or selfbot left/was removed from a guild.

Note

If the Guild is not found in the internal cache, then this event will not be called.

Parameters:

  • selfbot (SelfBot) – Selfbot that received an event from the websocket.

  • guild (Guild) – Deleted guild.

pynext.on_guild_emojis_update(selfbot, payload)#

Called when guild emojis will be updated.

Note

If the Guild is not found in the internal cache, then this event will not be called.

Parameters:

  • selfbot (SelfBot) – Selfbot that received an event from the websocket.

  • payload (EmojisUpdatePayload) – Emojis payload.

pynext.on_member_update(selfbot, old, new)#

Called when GuildMember was updated.

Note

If the Guild / Member is not found in the internal cache, then this event will not be called.

Parameters:

  • selfbot (SelfBot) – Selfbot that received an event from the websocket.

  • old (GuildMember) – Old guild member.

  • new (GuildMember) – New guild member.

pynext.on_guild_ban_create(selfbot, banentry)#

Called when User was banned from a guild.

Parameters:

  • selfbot (SelfBot) – Selfbot that received an event from the websocket.

  • banentry (BanEntry) – BanEntry object.

pynext.on_guild_ban_create(selfbot, banentry)#

Called when User was unbanned from a guild.

Parameters:

  • selfbot (SelfBot) – Selfbot that received an event from the websocket.

  • banentry (BanEntry) – Removed BanEntry object.

pynext.on_guild_role_create(selfbot, role)#

Called when someone create a role on the guild.

Parameters:

  • selfbot (SelfBot) – Selfbot that received an event from the websocket.

  • role (Role) – Created role.

pynext.on_guild_role_update(selfbot, old, new)#

Called when someone updates a guild role.

Note

If the Guild / Role is not found in the internal cache, then this event will not be called.

Parameters:

  • selfbot (SelfBot) – Selfbot that received an event from the websocket.

  • old (Role) – Old role object.

  • new (Role) – New role object.

pynext.on_guild_role_delete(selfbot, role)#

Called when someone delete a role on the guild.

Note

If the Guild is not found in the internal cache, then this event will not be called.

Parameters:

  • selfbot (SelfBot) – Selfbot that received an event from the websocket.

  • role (Role) – Deleted role.

pynext.on_http_ratelimit(payload)#

Called when the HTTP client reaches ratelimit.

Parameters:

payload (RatelimitPayload) – Ratelimit Payload.

pynext.on_websocket_raw_receive(response)#

Called when websocket receives a gateway response.

Note

Event is called only when the debug_events parameter is enabled in the PynextClient class.

Parameters:

response (GatewayResponse) – Raw gateway respo
